result.execSummary:
The defendant Joseph L Mason was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Conceal (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Joseph L Mason in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant Joseph L Mason in custody.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 and 1/2 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 and 1/2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS, concurrent with count 3 and any other sentence, credit for 154 days. 

AS TO COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced defendant to serve 100 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 2 and any other sentence.

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is NOT eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-Provide a DNA sample
-Pay mandatory Court costs and all applicable surcharges (including the DNA surcharge) and assessments to be collected by DOC at a rate which the department deems reasonable from the defendant's funds and during extended supervision; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Court waived all non-mandatory costs.
-Court set restitution in the amount of $5,295.00 made payable to MR.  Court orders restitution to be paid first.

Defendant advised that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Joseph L Mason in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant Joseph L Mason in custody.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.  
Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed and read-in to case for the purpose of sentencing.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:  Defendant changes his/her plea to GUILTY. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he/she must submit a DNA sample and may never possess a firearm, ammunition or body armor. Court advised defendant that his/her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his/her civil rights are restored.
